	<h1 style="font-size: 75px; text-align: center; background-color: black; color: white;">XML TAGS</h1>


	<div id="XmlTagsIntro">
			<h1>What's an XML Tag?</h1>
			<p>An XML Tag is a special keyword that is used to define some value within a game.</p>
			<h1>How do I write an XML Tag?</h3>
			<p>Tags are defined by placing special keywords within brackets.</p>
			<p>1. One special keyword in our game is <i>TITLE</i>, which describes the Title of our game.</p>
			<p>2. To define a TITLE tag, we can write: </p>
			<p> &nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp <b>&ltTITLE&gt</b> </i></p></p>
			<p>3. After defining a TITLE tag, we need to close the tag by writing another TITLE tag (this time accompanied with a backslash before the special keyword.)</p>
			<p> &nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp <b>&lt/TITLE&gt</b></p>
			<p>4. The value of the TITLE tag itself, is whatever you write between the two tags. If I want the title of my game to be called Nhia's Funky adventures, I would write: </p>
			<p> &nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp <b>&ltTITLE&gt</b> Nhia's Funky Adventures <b>&lt/TITLE&gt</b></p>
	</div>

